  levelNumber: 21
  levelName: Xunantunich
  location: Cayo, Belize
  levelDescription: "From the Stone Woman\u2019s pyramid, Xunantunich gazes across
    jungle and sky.\n\nXunantunich, meaning \u201CStone Woman\u201D in Maya, is an
    ancient city located near the Mopan River in western Belize. It flourished during
    the Late Classic period (c. 600\u2013900 AD) and served as a ceremonial and political
    center.\r\n\r\nThe site\u2019s most famous structure is El Castillo, a towering
    pyramid that rises about 40 meters, making it one of the tallest buildings in
    Belize. Its carved friezes depict gods, celestial symbols, and geometric patterns,
    reflecting Maya artistry and cosmology.\r\n\r\nXunantunich was part of a network
    of Maya cities, likely allied with nearby centers like Naranjo in Guatemala.
    Archaeologists have uncovered royal tombs, pottery, and jade ornaments, showing
    its importance in regional trade and ritual life.\r\n\r\nToday, visitors climb
    El Castillo to see sweeping views of the Belizean jungle and the Guatemalan border,
    where the ruins stand as a testament to Maya resilience and imagination."
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 6283ad06a6bf8bc49a02f05851b98dfa, type: 3}
